,Not Recommended,566990,29107641,Posted: 7 January,all,Timrod,"Russian Car Driver is a shovelware game that's not even a GOOD shovelware game. Taking heavily after ""skill-based"" driving games such as Driver and Gran Turismo, the game puts you in control of a boxy Russian sedan I call the Vladmobile.The Vladmobile is not governed by any of the laws of physics or common sense, something you'll figure out in the game's required first mode: Parking. Parking mode consists of navigating the Vladmobile through a path made out of traffic cones and stopping it in a glowing ""park zone"" within a time limit. What you'll soon figure out are two things:First, parking mode is really glitchy and a lot of the time it's easy to slip out of bounds between the cones (touching a cone automatically fails you) and slip back in at the park zone.Second, the Vladmobile does not accelerate or brake in a consistent manner. I spent probably ten minutes of the hour I played this game before refunding it figuring out exactly how the physics work. The answer is that they don't. The Vladmobile will not stop simply because you stopped pressing the accelerator or the reverse - you have to figure out that spacebar is the ""handbrake"" button, which causes the car to come to an absolute dead stop the second you use it. While the handbrake does make parking mode a lot easier, it's not something that comes naturally or is easy to figure out, especially if you're used to driving in games like Grand Theft Auto V that use realistic driving physics.Once you get past parking mode, you get to the game's second unlockable mode: drifting. Drifting mode is actually impossible with the default settings - you can't drift properly with the ""Anti-Lock Brakes"" and ""ESP Brakes"" settings on. With them off, the car goes from controlling like a 18th-century pirate ship to controlling like a stick of butter covered in bacon grease. Drifting mode is extremely easy to clear, since it uses the same course layout for all of the ""trials"" and the only differences are the time limit and the score you're expected to get. With all of the brake settings off, I was able to do this pretty much effortlessly by building up speed and then hitting left and right alternating until the game broke and gave me thousands of points.Oh, one thing I should mention about drifting mode: by default, the Vladmobile will not go over 60 miles per hour. To get it to go faster, you have to change the game to manual transmission - which uses controls not listed anywhere in the game itself (A upshifts gears by default, Z downshifts). However, manual transmission is a nightmare because being in the wrong gear for any period of time will cause your engine to explode, automatically failing whatever challenge you're on.Assuming you figure out parking and drifting mode, you then get to move on to the game's final mode, Drag Racing. Unlike Parking or Drifting, Drag Racing forces you to use manual transmission without any warning whatsoever, so if you have no experience with it you'll be wondering why your engine keeps exploding the second you touch the accelerator. I was completely and utterly unable to finish even the first stage of Drag Racing mode, mostly because of the terrible handling on the Vladmobile and the constant siege of oncoming traffic.The game is not good for speedrunning, it's not good for streaming, and it's certainly not fun. Don't think that because it cost you $0.69 that it's worth it - even paying that little promotes shovelware on Steam."
,Not Recommended,566990,29145711,Posted: 9 January,all,Rinaldootje,"Why did I even play this game for so long?I don't know.Russian Car Driver is... well tries to be a Rally driver racing game.I say tries to be, In reality it's a steaming pile of.....The grpahics are straight from a 2010 mobile game. And as you can see from the screenshots, this game is a port from a mobile game.But not just that, That game is even a port from a free to play online browser game (Just google ""Russian car driver HD"").And it's also available for free on Mobile Android devices.The gameplay is atrocious. Holding the gas pedan doesn't work half the time. Your car slips all over the place in unrealistic fashion. And the speedometer is clearly broken, saying I'm going 40kmph. While I still need 2 seconds to go past a concrete barrier about as long as my car.It doesn't even feel like 20 kmph.But mainly like I said this game is a Scam.You pay money for something you could play right now for free in your browser, Or on your mobile phones.Avoid it like the plague."
