,Not Recommended,566990,29143317,Posted: 9 January,all,oneoftheother,"The idea of this game is not necessarily like the title. Yes, the VAZ 2108 'Vladmobile' is Russian, but that's the only car included. It means what it says ""Russain Car Driver"", that's it - you drive A Russian car. The game howerver, is centered around the 2108. There are little icons placed all around with some short facts or history about it and an accompanying picture. I think the free roam mode was my favorite if I had to have one. The translations could use some work in the story mode, so could the auto transmission in general. For some odd reason, it shifts into neural every time it tries to upshift. It even has this problem in manual mode, which is really weird considering the in-game trans relies on user input. I can only assume that it's because of the clutch. The cars don't deform much graphically, but it is funny to drive around with the front wheels literally in the front. I like that some objects around the world are movable, and there's a way from one map to another. The textures aren't the greatest, but what can you expect from a .99 game? They remind me of gmod in a way, so it doesn't bother me that much. I enjoy the radio, I don't usually listen to Russian rap/hip-hop. It really improves the Russianness of this game. I have yet to unlock the custom paints, but it's nice to be able to change the default collor of the car. As Timrod put it,#Discussions_QuoteBlock_AuthorDrifting mode is actually impossible with the default settings - you can't drift properly with the ""Anti-Lock Brakes"" and ""ESP Brakes"" settings on. With them off, the car goes from controlling like a 18th-century pirate ship to controlling like a stick of butter covered in bacon grease.I recommend you turn all the car's aids off, and use man mode for ultimate usability. Try to shift around 2-3 on the revs, anything over will stop it. As others have noted, the police will not chase you for more than a few seconds. I'm really disappointed by this, another broken mechanic. It might be fixable through the game's files, but I don't care enough to look into it. As far as I'm concerned, I paid for the musicI guess, and bits of history I could have found with Google if I was really that adamant to learn about it. This game still needs work, but it could turn into something interesting. Include more VAZ cars, their history, fix the transmission, and police chases. Then this would be acceptable to release."
