,Recommended,566990,29760986,Posted: 7 February,all,MacDonald CSOFFER.ME,"Note - Steam needs a ""Meh"" option for reviews. I don't recommend it but I don't despise it either.For some weird reason, I actually kind of like this game. It's dirt cheap and does not belong on steam by any strech of the imagination. However, I find myself drawn to it in a peculiar way.Saying that this game is ""A little wonky"" is an understatement. The handling is a bit crap and the physics would make Newton turn in his grave. When you hit an object you just stop abruptly and the police chases last for about two seconds before the Police give up and go back to watching the same 4 GopnikMobiles and a bus drive round. The game also features theGoogle Translate Seal of Qualityas the english translation is in the same league asBig Rigs.This would normally qualify the game for the thumbs down but it does have some redeeming qualites.The car is reasonably well modeled given the price and there is some basic deformation. Mud and such can get stuck on your car dynamically and the environments do look like Russia. Although, there are some tell tale signs that pre-made assets have been used. Some of the bulidings look like they were ripped straight fromARMA IIand the cows are straight-up default Unity3D cows. However, these assets (If the dev is asset flipping) are cohesively used so I don't really have a problem with them.The music is quite clearly some Royalty-Free stuff but it's not (Too) terrible. It does the job it's supposed to do.It's quite clear that Falcoware has put the most effort into this game and for a free android game, it's alright.However, this is steam and by steams standards, this game is utter♥♥♥♥♥♥♥Overall verdict - Middle of the road, it's not good and not bad, 7/10Edit - My views have changed as of 16/06/2107, this game is a masterpiece"
